  <tr><td><strong>Blood Moon mutant zombies</strong></td><td>Normal spawn rate</td><td>Double spawn rate</td></tr>
  <tr><td><strong>Ender Dragon HP</strong></td><td>100 HP</td><td>1000 HP</td></tr>
  <tr><td><strong>Enderman and water</strong></td><td>Afraid of water (vanilla)</td><td>NOT afraid of water!</td></tr>
  <tr><td><strong>Death</strong></td><td>Respawn possible</td><td>Permadeath — world is deleted</td></tr>
  <tr><td><strong>Post-death debuff</strong></td><td colspan="2">Both modes: <strong>Severe Injury</strong> status effect applied on respawn <abbr class="src-cl" title="Source: mod changelog (mcmod.cn) — not personally verified">📜 changelog</abbr></td></tr>
  <tr><td><strong>Zombie revival</strong></td><td>❌ No</td><td>✅ Killed zombies may return <abbr class="src-cl" title="Source: mod changelog (mcmod.cn) — not personally verified">📜 changelog</abbr></td></tr>
  <tr><td><strong>Witch spawning</strong></td><td>✅ Normal</td><td>❌ Witches do not spawn <abbr class="src-cl" title="Source: mod changelog (mcmod.cn) — not personally verified">📜 changelog</abbr></td></tr>
  <tr><td><strong>Difficulty</strong></td><td>Ideal for learning</td><td>Ultimate, uncompromising challenge</td></tr>
</table>
<div class="tip-card">💡 <strong>Advice:</strong> If you're new to MITE:BE, <strong>start in Simple mode</strong> to learn. Hardcore mode is for experienced players — the mechanical differences are significant, and one mistake is permanent!</div>

<h4>Hunger & Thirst</h4>
<p>In MITE:BE, eating alone isn't enough — your character also has a <strong>thirst</strong> meter. You'll need to craft a water bag, and the water's purity matters too (filter paper is needed for clean water).</p>

<h4>Nutrition System</h4>
<p>Every food item has detailed stats: <strong>Satiation, Nutrition, Sugar, Protein, Phytonutrients, Insulin Response</strong>, and <strong>Hydration</strong>. Eating only one type of food causes <em>Malnourishment</em> (slow healing, +50% hunger drain). You need a balanced diet of protein (meat, milk), phytonutrients (fruits, vegetables), and sugar!</p>

<h4 id="temperature">Body Temperature</h4>
<p>Optimal body temperature is 36–37°C. Fire, lava, and the Nether raise it — water, rain, and ice lower it. Sunstroke and freezing are real dangers.</p>
<table class="compare-table">
