  <tr><td>96,000</td><td>Moderate</td><td>80–120 min</td><td>Nausea II (20s) after each sweet food</td></tr>
  <tr><td>144,000</td><td>Severe</td><td>120–160 min</td><td>Nausea III + Poison (5–10s) after each sweet food</td></tr>
</table>
<h4>Heat Stroke</h4>
<p>Being in a desert for 60+ seconds, or near lava (within 2 blocks) for 40+ seconds: <strong>Weakness II + Slowness II</strong> + food provides no nutrition (indefinitely until cured). Cure: bowl of hot water or sugar water.</p>

<h4>Quality System</h4>
<p>Crafted items have <strong>quality tiers</strong>. Right-click to select a higher quality (costs more XP). Quality primarily affects <strong>durability</strong>:</p>
<table>
  <tr><th>Quality</th><th>Description</th></tr>
  <tr><td style="color:#888">Wretched</td><td>Worst durability — avoid if possible</td></tr>
  <tr><td style="color:#aaa">Poor</td><td>Below-average durability</td></tr>
  <tr><td style="color:#ccc">Average</td><td>Base durability, free</td></tr>
  <tr><td style="color:var(--green)">Fine</td><td>Slightly more durable</td></tr>
  <tr><td style="color:var(--gold)">Excellent</td><td>Noticeably more durable</td></tr>
  <tr><td style="color:var(--accent2)">Superb</td><td>Significantly more durable</td></tr>
  <tr><td style="color:var(--mithril)">Masterwork</td><td>Outstanding durability</td></tr>
  <tr><td style="color:var(--adamantium)">Legendary</td><td>Maximum durability</td></tr>
</table>

<h4>XP Costs</h4>
<p><strong>Normal quality crafting is free (0 XP).</strong> Only higher quality tiers cost XP, and the benefit is primarily increased <strong>durability</strong>. Plan your XP budget wisely!</p>

