<h2 id="quickstart">Quick Start — Day 1 Essentials</h2>
<p>Days are short. Don't try to do everything — the only goal of day 1 is: <strong>survive the first night</strong>. Follow this order!</p>

<div class="info-box">🎯 <strong>Day 1 priorities (in this order):</strong>
<ol style="margin:6px 0 0 0">
  <li>Check your <strong>biome</strong> — ocean: start a new world immediately</li>
  <li>Break <strong>tall grass</strong> → get at least <strong>4 Plant Fiber</strong> (for Straw Rope)</li>
  <li>Break <strong>gravel by hand</strong> (harvest level 0!) → ~10% chance to drop <strong>Flint</strong> → 1 Flint = 4 Flint Shards → <strong>Simple Stone Knife</strong></li>
  <li>Pick up <strong>sticks from the ground</strong> (fallen branches under trees)</li>
  <li>Kill an animal → <strong>food + leather</strong></li>
  <li><strong>Before dark: climb a tree</strong> → floating tree base (see below)</li>
</ol></div>

<div class="warning-box">🌙 <strong>Wood chopping and the Workbench — those are Day 2 tasks!</strong> On day 1 just focus on gravel, food, plant fiber, sticks, and leather — everything else can wait. Days are very short, don't waste time!</div>
<div class="info-box">🎮 <strong>Mode difference:</strong> In Hardcore mode, less gravel generates (<strong>55%</strong> chance vs Simple <strong>75%</strong>). You'll need to mine more gravel for the same amount of flint!</div>

<div class="info-box">🎮 <strong>In Hardcore mode:</strong> Leaves are passable, so you'll fall through them when climbing. Bring <strong>extra sand/gravel</strong> to pillar up onto the trunk top and build outward above the canopy!</div>
<div class="info-box">🌳 <strong>Floating Tree Base — Best Night 1 Method:</strong><br>
Only <strong>5 sand or gravel blocks</strong> needed (hand-mineable!):
<ol style="margin:8px 0 0 18px">
  <li>Find a tree and climb to the top</li>
  <li>Remove the <strong>2 bottom logs</strong> of the tree — spiders can no longer reach the trunk to climb up</li>
  <li>At the treetop, place <strong>1 sand/gravel block under yourself</strong> + <strong>4 around you</strong></li>
  <li>Crouch/lie down — arrows fly over you, zombies can't knock anything out</li>
</ol>
<strong>Why it works:</strong> Arrows miss you (low profile). Zombies can't break anything. Spiders can't climb a floating tree. In the morning, just jump down.</div>

<div class="tip-card">🕯️ <strong>You probably won't have torches on night 1</strong> — that's completely normal! Without a Flint Pickaxe and coal ore, torches aren't possible yet. You're safe on the treetop even in total darkness.</div>

<!-- ===== PHASE GUIDE ===== -->

<h2 id="phase-guide">Phase Guide — The Full Game Progression</h2>
<p>MITE:BE progression is divided into three major phases. This guide shows you the <strong>correct order</strong>, the goals of each phase, and the critical milestones where your progress can get blocked.</p>

<div class="tip-card">💡 <strong>Tip:</strong> This guide summarizes order and goals only — find detailed recipes and descriptions in the other wiki sections.</div>

<h3 id="early-game">🌱 Early Game — From Flint to First Copper Tools</h3>
<p><strong>Goal:</strong> fire, shelter, the first furnace, and the first copper tools.</p>

<div class="info-box"><strong>⏱️ Day 1 Priorities (in this order!):</strong>
<ol style="margin:6px 0 0 0">
  <li>Collect <strong>plant fiber</strong> (tall grass) → <strong>Straw Rope</strong></li>
  <li>Collect <strong>gravel</strong> → flint chips → <strong>Basic Flint Knife</strong></li>
  <li>Flint Knife + Wood Log → <strong>Flint Workbench</strong> (unlocks 3×3 crafting!)</li>
  <li>At workbench: <strong>Wood Shovel</strong>, basic tools</li>
  <li>Find animals → collect <strong>leather</strong></li>
  <li><strong>Before dark: build shelter and make fire!</strong></li>
</ol></div>

<h4>Early game checklist (Days 1–14)</h4>
<table class="compare-table">
  <tr><th>Priority</th><th>Task</th><th>Why it matters</th></tr>
  <tr><td>🔴 Required</td><td><strong>Sieve</strong> construction</td><td>Ore particles from gravel → no sieve = no metals</td></tr>
  <tr><td>🔴 Required</td><td><strong>Clay Furnace</strong> + Campfire</td><td>First smelting + temperature control</td></tr>
  <tr><td>🔴 Required</td><td><strong>Obsidian Ingot Mold</strong></td><td>1 ingot = 9 ore particles — efficient smelting</td></tr>
  <tr><td>🟡 Important</td><td><strong>Hardened Clay Furnace</strong></td><td>Preparation for heat level 2 (copper smelting)</td></tr>
  <tr><td>🟡 Important</td><td><strong>Copper Workbench</strong></td><td>Unlocks copper-tier recipes</td></tr>
  <tr><td>🟡 Important</td><td>Full <strong>copper tool set</strong></td><td>Efficient mining and combat</td></tr>
  <tr><td>🟡 Important</td><td>Full <strong>copper armor</strong></td><td>Protection in caves and at night</td></tr>
  <tr><td>🟢 Needed</td><td><strong>Water Flask</strong> + filter paper</td><td>Thirst management — critical for survival!</td></tr>
</table>

<div class="warning-box">⚠️ <strong>Most common early game deaths:</strong>
<ul style="margin:4px 0 0 0">
  <li>Going outside at night without shelter (especially on the first night)</li>
  <li>Eating only fruit without protein → Malnutrition debuff</li>
  <li>Not making fire → freezing to death</li>
  <li>Going into caves before getting copper armor</li>
</ul></div>

<h3 id="mid-game">⚒️ Mid Game — From Silver to the Iron Pickaxe</h3>
<p><strong>Goal:</strong> the <strong>Multiblock Furnace</strong> (heat 2) and the <strong>Iron Pickaxe</strong> — these unlock the path to Hardstone.</p>

<h4>Mid game checklist (Days 15–40)</h4>
<table class="compare-table">
  <tr><th>Priority</th><th>Task</th><th>Why it matters</th></tr>
  <tr><td>🔴 Required</td><td>Learn <strong>Miner profession</strong></td><td>Direct ore block smelting REQUIRES this!</td></tr>
  <tr><td>🔴 Required</td><td>Craft <strong>Stone Furnace Core</strong></td><td>8× Stone Block + Copper/Silver Workbench = heat 2</td></tr>
  <tr><td>🔴 Required</td><td>Build <strong>Multiblock Furnace</strong> (stone)</td><td>Iron smelting is ONLY possible at heat level 2!</td></tr>
  <tr><td>🔴 Required</td><td><strong>Iron Pickaxe</strong></td><td>Required for mining Hardstone and Mithril ore (harvest 3)</td></tr>
  <tr><td>🟡 Important</td><td>Silver + alloys (Bronze, Silver-Copper)</td><td>Stronger than pure copper; silver: +bonus vs undead</td></tr>
  <tr><td>🟡 Important</td><td>Gold tools (transitional tier)</td><td>Gold Workbench needed for Obsidian Furnace Core</td></tr>
  <tr><td>🟡 Important</td><td>Iron Workbench + High Carbon Steel</td><td>Iron + Carbon = stronger than plain iron</td></tr>
  <tr><td>🟢 Needed</td><td>Learn <strong>Smithing profession</strong></td><td>Needed for metal item quality and crafting metal bars</td></tr>
</table>

<div class="warning-box">⚠️ <strong>Most common mid-game stalling points:</strong>
<ul style="margin:4px 0 0 0">
  <li>No Multiblock Furnace → iron smelting simply won't work!</li>
  <li>No Miner profession → ore block smelting won't work!</li>
  <li>Trying to mine Hardstone without an Iron Pickaxe → block cannot be mined</li>
  <li>Running out of coal → heat level 2 requires coal (wood/charcoal not enough!)</li>
</ul></div>

<h3 id="end-game">🔥 End Game — From Hardstone to the Ender Dragon</h3>
<p><strong>Goal:</strong> Full adamantium gear + defeat the Ender Dragon.</p>

<h4>End game checklist</h4>
<table class="compare-table">
