<h3 id="end-dimension">⬛ The End Dimension</h3>
<p>Reaching the End dimension in MITE:BE is fundamentally different from vanilla Minecraft. There is no classic Ender Eye → End Fortress combination.</p>
<h4>Entry Process</h4>
<ol>
  <li><strong>Defeat the Wither Boss</strong> → obtain the Nether Star</li>
  <li><strong>Build the Core Breaker</strong> from the Nether Star (Bedrock Pulverizer recipe)</li>
  <li>Go deep into the <strong>Nether</strong> → find the Core Block (lava texture, light level 15)</li>
  <li>The Core Block can only be mined with an <strong>Adamantium Pickaxe</strong> (other pickaxes can't reach it)</li>
  <li>Activate the Core Breaker on the Core Block → <strong>End Portal opens</strong></li>
</ol>
<div class="warning-box">⚠️ <strong>Core Block danger:</strong> The Core Block deals <strong>continuous lava damage within 8 blocks!</strong> Fire Resistance potion and strong armor required before approaching.</div>

<h4>Inside the End</h4>
<ul>
  <li><strong>Endermen</strong> — dangerous; fear water in Simple mode, but <strong>do NOT fear water in Hardcore mode!</strong></li>
  <li><strong>Ender Dragon</strong> — Simple: 100 HP, Hardcore: <strong>1,000 HP</strong></li>
  <li><strong>End Crystals</strong> — can be efficiently destroyed with Adamantium pickaxe or arrows</li>
  <li><strong>Enhanced Eye of Ender</strong> — a special item connected to the End dimension</li>
</ul>
<div class="tip-card">⚔️ <strong>Ender Dragon strategy:</strong> First destroy all End Crystals (shoot them with arrows from the obsidian towers), then attack the dragon. Full Adamantium armor + Mithril or Adamantium weapon recommended. Fire Resistance potion is helpful!</div>

