<!-- ===== BIOME GUIDE ===== -->

<h2 id="biomes">Biome Guide — Where to Start and What to Watch For</h2>
<p>In MITE:BE, your <strong>starting biome is one of the most important factors</strong> for your survival chances. Some biomes mean instant death or a forced new world restart, while others provide natural shelter and resources for the critical first night.</p>

<h3>🗺️ Biome Rating Table</h3>
<table>
  <tr><th>Biome</th><th>Rating</th><th>Reason</th></tr>
  <tr><td><strong>Hills / Extreme Hills</strong></td><td>✅ Best</td><td>Surface stone everywhere, many trees for the floating base method, natural cover</td></tr>
  <tr><td><strong>Forest</strong></td><td>✅ Best</td><td>Trees everywhere — ideal for the floating tree base night 1 method!</td></tr>
  <tr><td><strong>Taiga / Snowy Taiga</strong></td><td>⚠️ Medium</td><td>Trees available, but <strong>cold = faster temperature drain</strong></td></tr>
  <tr><td><strong>Plains</strong></td><td>⚠️ Medium</td><td>Open terrain, little natural cover — mobs approach from all directions</td></tr>
  <tr><td><strong>Desert</strong></td><td>⚠️ Hard</td><td>No wood, sand is a poor building material, hot climate</td></tr>
  <tr><td><strong>Jungle</strong></td><td>⚠️ Hard</td><td>Trees exist but the terrain is chaotic, navigation is difficult</td></tr>
  <tr><td><strong>Swamp / River</strong></td><td>❌ Avoid</td><td>Water slows movement, little solid ground, many mob spawns</td></tr>
  <tr><td><strong>Ocean</strong></td><td>🚫 START NEW WORLD</td><td>No reachable solid ground — unsurvivable start</td></tr>
  <tr><td><strong>Deep Ocean</strong></td><td>🚫 START NEW WORLD</td><td>Same as ocean but deeper — even worse</td></tr>
</table>

<div class="warning-box">🌊 <strong>Ocean biome = Start a new world immediately!</strong><br>If you spawn in an ocean, save your time — start a new world right away. No wood, no stone, water everywhere, and aquatic creatures attack at night. There is no way out.</div>

<h3>🔦 Torch Burnout — Critical Mechanic</h3>
<div class="warning-box">🎮 <strong>Mode difference:</strong> In Simple mode, torches <strong>do NOT burn out over time</strong> (the 3-day timer is disabled). <strong>However, rain DOES extinguish torches even in Simple mode!</strong> In Hardcore mode, both are active: torches burn out after 3 days AND rain extinguishes them.</div>
<p>In MITE:BE, placed torches burn out after <strong>3 in-game days</strong>. This is one of the most dangerous early-game mechanics:</p>
<ul>
  <li>If a torch by your shelter entrance burns out, that area goes dark — <strong>mobs can spawn there</strong></li>
  <li>If torches inside your shelter burn out, monsters can appear inside too</li>
  <li>To relight a torch you need <strong>Flint and Steel</strong></li>
  <li><strong>Always carry Flint and Steel at night!</strong> Getting caught in a dark shelter is often fatal</li>
  <li>⚡ <strong>Exception: Torches in Plains biomes never burn out!</strong></li>
  <li>🌧️ <strong>Rain extinguishes torches</strong> — in both game modes! If your torches are outdoors, you'll need to relight them after rain</li>
</ul>
<div class="tip-card">💡 <strong>Tip:</strong> Craft Flint and Steel as soon as you have copper smelting (earliest: Copper Flint and Steel = Copper Nugget + Flint). Until then, place torches under a roof to protect from rain! Always carry it at night — failing to relight burned-out torches is one of the most common early-game deaths.</div>

<h3>🧟 Pickaxe Zombies — The Enemy of Hiding</h3>
<div class="warning-box">⛏️ <strong>Pickaxe zombies can mine through ANY block at ground level — including cobblestone and obsidian!</strong><br>There is no block that will stop a pickaxe zombie group at the surface. Cobblestone walls, stone hillsides, even obsidian — none of it is safe. If you hear scraping sounds on your walls at night, pickaxe zombies are outside.</div>
<p><strong>The only reliable early-game solution:</strong> don't stay on the ground! The <strong>Floating Tree Base</strong> is the only safe method for the first night — zombies cannot climb trees (see above).</p>

<h3>🧠 Mob AI — They Can Sense You Through Walls</h3>
<p>Mob AI in MITE:BE has been fundamentally changed from vanilla Minecraft:</p>
<ul>
  <li><strong>Proximity-based detection:</strong> Mobs can sense you through walls — <em>they don't need to see you to know you're there</em>. A single stone wall does not create a safe zone</li>
  <li><strong>Hiding barely works:</strong> Especially during mass nighttime spawns, mobs quickly find you in shallow hideouts</li>
  <li><strong>Group behavior:</strong> When one mob finds you, others are attracted quickly</li>
</ul>
<div class="info-box">⚠️ <strong>Mindset shift required:</strong> Unlike vanilla Minecraft, <em>simply &quot;hiding in a hole&quot; is not enough</em>. Real safety only comes from a deep, sealed, and well-lit shelter.</div>

<h3>🏕️ Proven Shelter Strategies</h3>
<div class="info-box">🎮 <strong>Hardcore difference:</strong> In Hardcore mode, <strong>leaves are passable</strong> — you'll fall through them when climbing. The method still works, but bring <strong>extra sand/gravel</strong> to pillar up the trunk and build outward above the canopy!</div>
<div class="info-box"><strong>🌳 Floating Tree Base (Best Night 1 Method):</strong><br>
The best method for the first night — only 5 sand or gravel blocks needed:
<ol style="margin:8px 0 0 18px">
  <li>Find a tree and climb to the top</li>
  <li>Remove the <strong>2 bottom logs</strong> of the tree — spiders can no longer reach the trunk to climb</li>
  <li>At the treetop: place <strong>1 sand/gravel block under yourself</strong> + <strong>4 around you</strong> (5 blocks total)</li>
  <li>Crouch/lie down — arrows fly over you, zombies can't knock anything out, spiders can't reach you</li>
</ol>
</div>
<div class="tip-card">💡 <strong>Upgrade:</strong> Once you have stone and wood, build a proper stone house. An <strong>Iron Door</strong> is the real durable protection against zombies and pickaxe variants — but that's a mid-game goal, not day 1 or 2.</div>

<h3>🎭 Biome-Specific Mob Variants</h3>
<p>In some biomes, stronger or modified variants of base mobs spawn:</p>
<table>
  <tr><th>Biome</th><th>Variant Mobs</th></tr>
  <tr><td><strong>Plains</strong></td><td>Plains Zombie, Plains Creeper, Plains Skeleton, Plains Spider</td></tr>
  <tr><td><strong>Snowy biomes</strong></td><td>Snowy Zombie, Snowy Creeper, Snowy Skeleton, Snowy Spider</td></tr>
  <tr><td><strong>Desert</strong></td><td>Desert Lord (boss-type mob)</td></tr>
</table>

