<!-- ===== FLINT AGE ===== --><h3>Common Mistakes & Pro Tips</h3>
<div class="tips-grid">
<div class="tip-card"><strong>Don't burn meat!</strong> Use a campfire or oven. Burnt meat causes poisoning!</div>
<div class="tip-card"><strong>Sieve regularly!</strong> Sieving is the primary way to get metal early. Don't neglect it!</div>
<div class="tip-card"><strong>Save your molds!</strong> Only 20 uses! Always keep a few spares.</div>
<div class="tip-card"><strong>Varied diet!</strong> One-sided nutrition causes Malnutrition. Eat meat, fruit, and vegetables!</div>
<div class="tip-card"><strong>Flint pick = coal!</strong> The flint pickaxe can mine coal ore, though at 1.5x durability cost.</div>
<div class="tip-card"><strong>Get leather rope early!</strong> Kill animals for leather as soon as you have a knife — leather rope is essential.</div>
<div class="tip-card"><strong>Filter water!</strong> Raw water can cause illness. Craft filter paper for clean water!</div>
<div class="tip-card"><strong>Workbench tier!</strong> Higher tier recipes need higher tier workbenches (copper, iron, etc.)</div>
<div class="tip-card"><strong>🐑 Sheep = top priority!</strong> White wool → String → String Mesh Sieve — fastest path to sieving, can skip the normal flint progression!</div>
<div class="tip-card"><strong>Pebbles are throwable!</strong> Holding a pebble lets you throw it at mobs. Useful in a pinch when you have no weapon.</div>
<div class="tip-card"><strong>Pebbles → Cobblestone!</strong> Pebbles can be crafted into cobblestone at a <strong>Silver Workbench</strong> — saves copper pickaxe durability on stone.</div>
</div>


<h2 id="flint-age">Flint Age</h2>
