<h2 id="alloying">Alloying System (Alloying Furnace)</h2>
<p>In MITE:BE, standard metal equipment can be <strong>upgraded further through alloying</strong> in an Alloying Furnace. Alloying does NOT smelt raw ingots into alloys — it transforms existing, <strong>full-durability equipment pieces</strong>.</p>
<div class="warning-box">⚠️ <strong>Critical rule:</strong> Only <strong>100% durability (undamaged)</strong> tools and armor can be alloyed! Damaged items cannot be processed.</div>

<h3>Crafting the Alloying Furnace</h3>
<table class="compare-table">
  <tr><th>Recipe</th><th>Materials</th><th>Required Workbench</th></tr>
  <tr><td><strong>Copper (cheapest)</strong></td><td>4× Copper Ingot + 1× Stone Furnace</td><td>Copper Workbench</td></tr>
  <tr><td>Silver</td><td>4× Silver Ingot + 1× Stone Furnace</td><td>Copper Workbench</td></tr>
  <tr><td>Iron</td><td>6× Stone + 2× Iron Ingot + 1× Stone Furnace</td><td>Iron Workbench</td></tr>
</table>
<p><strong>Fuel accepted:</strong> Coal (30s), Coal Block (270s), Lava Bucket (120s). <strong>Stack limit:</strong> 1 per stack.</p>

