<h3>How to get Carbon Crystal</h3>
<p><strong>Spawns ONLY in Highland biome</strong>, Y0-20 (weight: 100 — the most common ore there!). Ways to obtain:</p>
<ul>
  <li>Mine Carbon Crystal Clusters (1 cluster = 4 shards)</li>
  <li>Smelt from Coal Blocks: 1 Coal Block → 1 Carbon Crystal Shard (in the Alloying Furnace)</li>
</ul>
<div class="tip-card">💡 <strong>Mercury Cauldron upgrade (Ancient Metal armor):</strong> Right-click a Mercury Cauldron (place Cauldron from swamp hut over a lava source, add Mercury Ore) with a full-durability Ancient Metal armor piece → when the complete set is worn, body temperature stays completely stable! This upgrade is independent of the Alloying Furnace.</div>
<div class="info-box">📝 <strong>Other alloys:</strong> According to the official mcmod.cn database, <em>only</em> the 3 alloys above exist in the Alloying Furnace. Hardstone, Mithril and Adamantium equipment cannot be alloyed — they come from standard large furnaces.</div>


<h2 id="food">Food & Nutrition</h2>
<p>Diet variety is critical in MITE:BE! One-sided eating causes Malnourishment. Press <strong>P</strong> to open the nutrition screen!</p>

<div class="info-box">🤕 <strong>Getting headache damage?</strong> If your character is taking periodic damage from a headache debuff, it's almost certainly an <strong>unbalanced diet</strong>. Eat a salad: <strong>Bowl + 3× Dandelion</strong> (or any other vegetable). Press P to check your nutrition breakdown!</div>

