<h3>Material Durability Multipliers</h3>
<p>Every item's durability is calculated by applying a material multiplier to a base value. Leather is the baseline (1×).</p>
<div id="material-durability-mult"></div>
<div class="info-box">💡 <strong>Tip:</strong> Adamantium has 256× the durability of leather — making it incredibly durable. Even Iron (8×) vs Wood (0.5×) means iron tools last <em>16× longer</em> than wooden ones.</div>

