<h2 id="caves">Caves & Mining</h2>
<p>Areas below Y=35 are dangerous but resource-rich cave systems. Here you'll find rare ores and carbon crystals.</p>

<div class="tip">Craft a Mining Helmet for a better light source — excellent for underground exploration! (Unlocked via knowledge book.)</div>

<h3>Tool Levels — Which Pickaxe for Which Ore?</h3>
<p>In MITE:BE, every block has a <strong>harvest level</strong>. A lower-level pickaxe cannot mine the block — it just breaks slowly and drops nothing!</p>
<table class="compare-table">
  <tr><th>Level</th><th>Tools</th><th>Mineable Blocks</th></tr>
  <tr>
    <td><strong>1 — Flint/Rock</strong></td>
    <td>Flint Pickaxe, Rock Pickaxe, Flint Mattock, Flint Axe</td>
    <td>Logs, Sandstone, Glass, Ice, Hardened Clay, Sandstone Stalactites</td>
  </tr>
  <tr>
    <td><strong>2 — Copper/Silver tier</strong></td>
    <td>Copper, Silver, Gold, Bronze, Silver-Copper, Obsidian, Rusted Iron pickaxe</td>
    <td><strong>Stone</strong>, Coal/Iron/Gold/Copper/Silver/Lapis/Redstone ore, Copper/Silver blocks</td>
  </tr>
  <tr>
    <td><strong>3 — Iron tier</strong></td>
    <td>Iron, Ancient Metal, Hardstone, High Carbon Steel pickaxe</td>
    <td><strong>Obsidian</strong>, Emerald ore, <strong>Mithril ore</strong>, <strong>Hardstone ore</strong>, Gold block (3), Iron block (4!)</td>
  </tr>
  <tr>
    <td><strong>4 — Mithril tier</strong></td>
    <td>Mithril pickaxe</td>
    <td><strong>Diamond ore</strong>, <strong>Adamantium ore</strong>, Iron block, Hardstone block (4)</td>
  </tr>
  <tr>
    <td><strong>5 — Adamantium tier</strong></td>
    <td>Adamantium pickaxe</td>
    <td>Diamond block (5), Mithril block (5)</td>
  </tr>
  <tr>
    <td><strong>100 — Bedrock</strong></td>
    <td>Bedrock Pulverizer only</td>
    <td>Bedrock</td>
  </tr>
</table>
<div class="warning-box"><strong>⚠️ Critical:</strong> You <em>cannot</em> mine Diamond Ore with an Iron Pickaxe! You need a Mithril Pickaxe. Same for Adamantium Ore. This is why reaching the Mithril age is a major breakthrough.</div>

