<h3>Natural Wonders</h3>
<p>Stalactites, stalagmites, glow mushrooms, glow weeds, ice mushrooms, and icicles decorate the caves. The <strong>Red Crystal Cave</strong> appears as a special biome (unlocks after day 32).</p>


<!-- ===== UNDERGROUND ===== -->

<h2 id="underground">Underground Dimension</h2>
<p>In MITE:BE, the Underground is a <strong>separate dimension</strong> beneath the overworld. To enter, build an <strong>Obsidian portal on the bedrock layer</strong> in the overworld and light it with Flint and Steel.</p>

<div class="warning-box">⚠️ The Underground is rich in ores but filled with mutant monsters! At least <strong>full Iron gear</strong> recommended before entry. Always prepare an escape route!</div>

<h3>Structures</h3>
<ul>
  <li><strong>Red Crystal Cave</strong> — rare biome that unlocks after day 32. Contains valuable crystals.</li>
  <li><strong>Emerald Forest</strong> — underground forest biome with glowing mushrooms and unique vegetation. Emerald ore is more common here.</li>
  <li><strong>Mushroom Forest Battle Tower</strong> — fortified structure in mushroom forest biome. Contains loot chests and powerful guardians.</li>
  <li><strong>Cave decorations:</strong> stalactites, stalagmites, glowing mushrooms, glowing grass, icy mushrooms, and icicles adorn the caves.</li>
</ul>

