<div class="info-box">⛏️ <strong>Earth Elementals:</strong> Come in 5 variants (dirt, stone, sand, gravel, clay). Can only be effectively damaged with a pickaxe — swords barely work! The pickaxe material must be at least as strong as the elemental's type.</div>

<h3>Environmental Hazards</h3>
<ul>
  <li><strong>Eternal darkness:</strong> No natural sunlight in the Underground. Torches and glowing mushrooms are the only light sources.</li>
  <li><strong>Flying Ash:</strong> In certain areas, ash floats in the air, reducing visibility.</li>
  <li><strong>Fog:</strong> Some caves have thick fog that makes navigation difficult.</li>
  <li><strong>Increased lava:</strong> More lava pools and lava streams than in the overworld.</li>
  <li><strong>Double spawners:</strong> At deep levels, mob spawner blocks appear in pairs.</li>
</ul>

<h3>Strategy Tips</h3>
<div class="tip-card">💡 <strong>Preparing for the Underground:</strong>
<ul style="margin:4px 0 0 0">
  <li>Minimum <strong>full Iron armor and weapons</strong> — Hardstone/Ancient Metal recommended for deeper levels</li>
  <li>Bring at least <strong>64 torches</strong> and <strong>Flint and Steel</strong></li>
  <li>Always mark your return path (torches on the left → follow right side going back)</li>
  <li>Build a <strong>Return Portal</strong> before going too deep (Obsidian frame underground → returns to overworld)</li>
  <li><strong>Ancient Metal sword</strong> is essential against Phase Spiders — no other weapon works!</li>
  <li>Bring potions (Regeneration, Night Vision) if available</li>
</ul></div>

<h3>Underground → Nether Gateway</h3>
<p>At the deepest level of the Underground, in the <strong>bedrock layer</strong>, you'll find the <strong>Mantle</strong> — the gateway to the Nether dimension. Build a portal on the magma layer to reach the Nether.</p>
<div class="info-box">🔥 <strong>On Hard difficulty, there are 3 bedrock layers!</strong> Finding the Mantle may take longer.</div>


