<h2 id="nether">The Nether</h2>
<p>To reach the Nether, find the <strong>Mantle</strong> in the Underground's bedrock layer and place a portal.</p>
<div class="info">On Hard difficulty, there are 3 bedrock layers!</div>

<div class="warning-box">🔥 <strong>The Nether is the hardest dimension in the game!</strong> Full <strong>Mithril gear</strong> strongly recommended. Fire Resistance potion is mandatory against Fire Elementals and lava hazards. Do not enter unprepared!</div>

<h3>Nether Mobs</h3>
<table class="compare-table">
  <tr><th>Mob</th><th>HP</th><th>Damage</th><th>XP</th><th>Special</th></tr>
  <tr><td>Demon Spider</td><td>20</td><td>5</td><td>10</td><td>Fire resistant, poisonous</td></tr>
  <tr><td>Hell Hound</td><td>16</td><td>4</td><td>8</td><td>Fire resistant, fast, hunts in packs</td></tr>
  <tr><td>Infernal Creeper</td><td>20</td><td>—</td><td>10</td><td>Fire resistant, larger explosion</td></tr>
  <tr><td>Red Blaze</td><td>40</td><td>6</td><td>20</td><td><strong>6 fireballs at once!</strong> Drops Blaze Rods</td></tr>
  <tr><td>Fire Elemental</td><td>50</td><td>8</td><td>25</td><td><strong>3% instant kill</strong> on burning players! Water/snowballs/harming potions work</td></tr>
  <tr><td>Ghast</td><td>40</td><td>6 (fireball)</td><td>20</td><td>Huge, flying, fire-breathing — deflect its fireballs!</td></tr>
  <tr><td>Zombie Pigman</td><td>20</td><td>5</td><td>8</td><td>Neutral if wearing gold, otherwise immediately hostile</td></tr>
  <tr><td>Vampire/Giant Vampire Bat</td><td>6/30</td><td>2/6</td><td>3/15</td><td>Life steal</td></tr>
</table>
<div class="info-box">🔥 <strong>Fire Elemental:</strong> The most infamous Nether mob. If you are <strong>on fire</strong> when it attacks, there is a <strong>3% chance it instantly kills</strong> you! Enchanted items, water, snowballs, and Harming Potions work against it — fire and silver weapons do NOT. Fire Resistance potion is mandatory!</div>

<h3>Core Blocks</h3>
<p>Deep in the Nether you'll find <strong>Core Blocks</strong> — lava-textured blocks that emit light (light level 15).</p>
<ul>
  <li>Within <strong>8 blocks</strong>, they deal lava damage to the player (v0.8.0+)</li>
  <li>The only way to destroy them is with the <strong>Core Destroyer</strong></li>
  <li>Destroying a Core Block <strong>opens an End portal</strong> — this is the only way to the End dimension!</li>
</ul>
<div class="warning-box">⚠️ <strong>End Dimension:</strong> Destroying a Core Block (with the Core Destroyer) opens the End portal. This is the only entry point needed to defeat the Ender Dragon!</div>

<h3>Nether Resources</h3>
<ul>
  <li><strong>Netherrack:</strong> The Nether's base stone — needed for building the Netherrack Furnace (heat 4)</li>
  <li><strong>Blaze Rod:</strong> Dropped by Red Blazes — <strong>heat level 4 fuel</strong>, essential for Adamantium smelting!</li>
  <li><strong>Glowstone:</strong> Light source, also needed for potion brewing</li>
  <li><strong>Nether Quartz:</strong> Used in potion and enchanting recipes</li>
  <li><strong>Wither Rose:</strong> Found in Nether Fortress loot chests — needed to summon the Wither Boss</li>
</ul>

<h3>Nether Fortress</h3>
<p>Explore the Nether Fortress! Reward chests may contain <strong>Wither Rose</strong>.</p>

<h3>Strategy Tips</h3>
<div class="tip-card">💡 <strong>Nether survival guide:</strong>
<ul style="margin:4px 0 0 0">
  <li><strong>Fire Resistance potion</strong> is mandatory — Fire Elemental is nearly impossible without it</li>
  <li>Wear <strong>something Gold</strong> — Zombie Pigmen are immediately hostile without it</li>
  <li>Blaze farming: prepare for Blaze Rod hunting (Blaze Rods = key to Adamantium smelting)</li>
  <li>Lava bucket collection: the Nether has abundant lava, fill buckets for your furnaces</li>
  <li>Spare armor and weapons recommended — the Nether is lethal!</li>
</ul></div>

