<h3 id="portals">Portal Types</h3>
<p>MITE:BE has 5 portal types that teleport between different dimensions. Each portal requires an Obsidian frame and Flint and Steel.</p>
<table class="compare-table">
  <tr><th>#</th><th>Portal</th><th>Where to Build</th><th>Destination</th><th>Color</th></tr>
  <tr><td>1</td><td><strong>Normal Portal</strong></td><td>Overworld (no bedrock beneath)</td><td>World spawn point</td><td style="color:#88aaff">Blue</td></tr>
  <tr><td>2</td><td><strong>Nether Portal</strong></td><td>Overworld bedrock layer</td><td>Underground dimension</td><td style="color:#b388ff">Purple</td></tr>
  <tr><td>3</td><td><strong>Return Portal</strong></td><td>Anywhere in Underground</td><td>Overworld</td><td style="color:#4ecca3">Cyan</td></tr>
  <tr><td>4</td><td><strong>Hell Portal</strong></td><td>Underground magma layer</td><td>Nether dimension</td><td style="color:#ff5555">Red</td></tr>
  <tr><td>5</td><td><strong>Hell Return Portal</strong></td><td>Anywhere in the Nether</td><td>Underground dimension</td><td style="color:#b388ff">Purple</td></tr>
</table>
<div class="info-box">🔮 <strong>v0.9.0 special:</strong> Lighting a normal obsidian portal on the bedrock layer in the Overworld → 10 seconds of Nausea → after 5 seconds, all players are teleported to the ruins of a Pillager Fortress!</div>

<h3 id="biome-portals">Biome Portals (v0.8.0+)</h3>
<p>8 biome portals are available using <strong>Transmutation Stones</strong>. Each Transmutation Stone is crafted from its corresponding material + Obsidian on a regular workbench, then used in place of regular obsidian in the portal frame.</p>
<div class="warning-box">⚠️ <strong>v0.9.0 change:</strong> Biome portals <strong>no longer teleport near structures</strong> — they only bring you to general biome terrain at a random location. Each entry takes you somewhere different. To return home, no biome portal needed: any standard obsidian frame (NOT on bedrock) → returns to world Spawn.</div>
