<div class="tip-card">🗺️ <strong>Obsidian Generator:</strong> Place a <strong>Cauldron</strong> (found in swamp huts), right-click with any pickaxe → <strong>Double-Spout Cauldron</strong>. Lava on one side + water on the other → 1 obsidian generated every 120 seconds. Extremely useful in early game for portals!<br><strong>Lava furnace:</strong> Build your large furnace over a lava stream (or place a lava source block below) — free, permanent fuel for smelting.</div>


<!-- ===== ADAMANTIUM ===== -->

<h2 id="adamantium">Adamantium — From the Depths of Hell</h2>
<p>From the depths of the Nether, imbued with evil essence and terrible power. Mine adamantium ore with a <strong>mithril pickaxe/war hammer</strong>.</p>
<div class="warning-box">🔥 <strong>Smelting:</strong> Adamantium ore requires a <strong>Blaze Rod</strong> (heat level 4) AND a <strong>Netherrack Furnace</strong> — its melting point (6210°C) exceeds the Obsidian Furnace max (5000°C)! Miner profession also required.</div>

<p>Adamantium arrows are extremely useful — you'll need them to destroy End Crystals!</p>

<div class="tip">The adamantium pickaxe can also dig out the Bedrock Pulverizer!</div>


